{"title_page": "Zorin OS", "text_new": "{{Infobox OS\n| name = Zorin OS\n| logo = Zorin Logomark.svg\n| logo_size = 65px\n| logo alt = Zorin OS Logo\n| screenshot = File:Zorin OS 15.png\n| screenshot_size = 300px\n| screenshot_alt = Desktop of main version\n| caption = Zorin OS 15 desktop\n| collapsible = \n| version of = <!-- For articles about releases of operating systems ONLY -->\n| developer = Zorin Group\n| programmed in = [[C (programming language)|C]], [[C++]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]], [[D (programming language)|D]]\n| family = [[Linux]]\n| working state = Current\n| source model = [[Open-source software|Open-source]], some [[proprietary software|proprietary]] [[device driver|driver]]s\n| released = 2009\n| discontinued = <!-- DON'T use this for articles about releases of operating systems -->\n| RTM date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} ONLY for articles about OS releases -->\n| GA date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} ONLY for articles about OS releases -->\n| latest release version = OS 15.2<ref name=OS15>{{cite web\n | url       = https://zoringroup.com/blog/2020/03/05/zorin-os-15-2-is-released-harder-better-faster-stronger/\n | title     = Zorin OS 15.2 is here\n | author1   = Zorin OS\n | publisher = Zorin Group\n | date      = 5 March 2020}}</ref>\n| latest release date = {{Start date and age|2020|03|5|df=yes}}\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} -->\n| marketing target = [[Personal computers]]\n| language = More than 50 languages <small>by [[#Local communities (LoCos)|LoCos]]</small>\n| update model = [[Software Updater]]\n| package manager = [[APT (Debian)|APT]], [[dpkg]], [[Snappy (package manager)|Snappy]], [[flatpak]]\n| supported platforms = x86_64, i686<ref name=distrowatch /><!-- IA-32, x64, Itanium, ARM etc. -->\n| kernel type = [[Monolithic kernel|Monolithic]]\n| userland = [[GNU]]\n| ui = [[GNOME]]\n| license = [[Free software]] licenses<br />(mainly [[GPL]])\n| website = {{URL|https://zorinos.com}}\n| support status = <!-- For articles about releases of operating systems ONLY -->\n| other articles = \n}}\n\n'''Zorin OS''' is a [[personal computer]] [[operating system]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.linux.com/learn/zorin-os-linux-distribution-windows-xp-and-7-fans |title=Zorin OS: The Linux Distribution for Windows XP and 7 Fans |website=linux.com |publisher=The Linux Foundation |date=2016-02-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcworld.com/article/2458046/10-reasons-to-try-zorin-os-9-the-linux-os-that-looks-like-windows.html |title=10 reasons to try Zorin OS 9, the Linux OS that looks like Windows |website=pcworld.com |publisher=PC World |date=2014-07-30 }}</ref> It is marketed as an operating system designed for users new to [[Linux|Linux-based]] computer systems. One of the operating system's built-in features allows users to change the interface to resemble those of [[Microsoft Windows]] or [[MacOS]].<ref name=zorinofficial>{{cite web|title=Zorin OS-Home|url=https://zorinos.com/|publisher=Zorin OS|accessdate=19 March 2016|quote=Zorin OS is a multi-functional operating system designed specifically for newcomers to Linux. It's based on Ubuntu Linux....The Look Changer lets you change your desktop to look and act like either Windows 7, XP, 2000, Ubuntu Unity, Mac OS X or GNOME 2 for ultimate ease of use.}}</ref><ref name=distrowatch>{{cite web |title=Zorin OS |url=https://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=zorin |website=DistroWatch.com |accessdate=25 October 2018 |language=English |date=2018-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Speed |first1=Richard |title=Linux 4.18 arrives fashionably late while Zorin OS shines up its Windows |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2018/08/14/zorin_and_linux/ |website=The Register |publisher=Situation Publishing |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=14 August 2018}}</ref> [[Wine (software)|Wine]] and [[PlayOnLinux]] can be easily installed in Zorin OS,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zorinos.com/help/install-apps/#windows-apps|title=Zorin OS: Install Apps|website=Zorin OS|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> allowing users to run Windows software for ease of transition and gaming. Zorin OS' creators distribute different editions of the operating system; the \"Ultimate\" edition is for purchase.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Phillip|first1=Watt|title=Pro Freeware and Open Source Solutions for Business|publisher=Apress|page=218|url=https://books.google.com/?id=V1l4CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA218&dq=%22Zorin+OS%22#v=onepage&q=%22Zorin%20OS%22&f=false|isbn=9781484211304|date=2015-08-29}}</ref>\n\nIts current releases are Zorin OS 15.2 Ultimate, Zorin OS 15.2 Core, Zorin OS 15.2 Lite, and Zorin OS 15.2 Education. The new editions continue to use the Ubuntu-based Linux kernel and GNOME or XFCE interface.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnston |first1=Mike |title=Zorin OS 12 Review |url=https://www.cmscritic.com/zorin-os-12-review/ |publisher=CMS Critic |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=5 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Features==\nZorin OS is fully graphical along with a graphical installer. Zorin OS follows the Long-term releases of the main [[Ubuntu]] system for stability and security.\n\nZorin OS comes with its own repositories and historically with [[Ubuntu]]'s repositories as well.\n\n==About==\nZorin OS is a [[Linux distribution]]. The distribution aims to be user-friendly and be fully compatible with [[Ubuntu]]'s own base. Zorin OS has built-in features which allows users to change the interface to resemble those of Microsoft Windows or MacOS, which makes it easier to use.\n\n==History==\nZorin OS initially released on {{date|1 July 2009|DMY}}. The 12.x series was the last version of Zorin OS that required users to do a clean install. Since version 12.4, users were able to upgrade as normal via the systems update manager.\n\n===Version history===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Version !! Date !! Features/Notes !! Ref(s)\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 1.0}} || 1 July 2009 || Initial release ||rowspan=\"23\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://distrowatch.com/index.php?distribution=zorin |website=DistroWatch.com |title=Zorin news releases |publisher=Unsigned Integer Limited |accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS Limited Edition '09}} || 7 December 2009 || \n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 2}} || 1 January 2010 || 5 different varieties: Core, Gaming, Multimedia, Educational, Ultimate\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 3}} || 10 June 2010 || Zorin OS Look Changer added, installation slideshow tutorial\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 4}} || 22 December 2010 || Improved file manager, performance improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 5}} || 6 June 2011 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; new theme, updated software, Zorin-specific program improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 5.1|show=}} || 23 August 2011 || Updated Linux Kernel, aesthetic updates\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 6}} || 18 June 2012 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; new desktop environment, \"Zorin Look Changer\"\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 6.1}} || 8 November 2012 || Updated kernel & software, security updates\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 6.2}} || 27 February 2013 || \"Zorin Menu\" update, stability improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 6.3}} || 14 May 2013 || Updated kernel\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 7}} || 10 June 2013 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; updated software, Linux kernel 3.8, design overhaul\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 6.4}} || 28 August 2013 || Updated kernel and software\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 8}} || 27 January 2014 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; updated software, UI improvements, Zorin theme changer<ref>{{cite web |author1=Zorin OS |title=Zorin OS 8 Core and Ultimate are here |url=https://zoringroup.com/blog/2014/01/27/zorin-os-8-core-and-ultimate-are-here/ |publisher=Zorin Group |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=27 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 9}} || 15 July 2014 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; stability improvements, Firefox support, more themes\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 10}} || 1 August 2015 || Default application refresh, performance & security improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 11}} || 3 February 2016 || ''Core'' and ''Ultimate'' available; new default applications, desktop user experience overhaul\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 12}} || 18 November 2016 || New Zorin Desktop, activities overview, search revamp<ref>{{cite web |author1=Zorin OS |title=Zorin OS 12 Core and Ultimate Are Here: Our Biggest Release Ever |url=https://zoringroup.com/blog/2016/11/18/zorin-os-12-core-and-ultimate-are-here-our-biggest-release-ever-2/ |publisher=Zorin Group |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=18 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 12.1}} || 27 February 2017 || Bug fixes, new desktop features, performance improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 12.2}} || 8 September 2017 || Desktop refinements, performance and stability improvements\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 12.3}} || 16 March 2018 || Wine compatibility built-in, Direct3D 10 & 11 support<ref>{{cite web |author1=Zorin OS |title=Zorin OS 12.3 Released \u2013 A Stronger, More Versatile System |url=https://zoringroup.com/blog/2018/03/15/zorin-os-12-3-released-a-stronger-more-versatile-system/ |publisher=Zorin Group |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=15 March 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Version|o|Zorin OS 12.4}} || 13 September 2018 || Linux kernel 4.15, performance improvements, software update process streamlining<ref>{{cite web |author1=Zorin OS |title=Zorin OS 12.4 Released \u2013 More Secure and Compatible than Ever Before |url=https://zoringroup.com/blog/2018/08/13/zorin-os-12-4-released-more-secure-and-compatible-than-ever-before/ |publisher=Zorin Group |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Version|c|Zorin OS 15}} || 5 June 2019 || Performance improvements, Zorin Connect (Android sync notifications), New desktop theme, Touch Layout functions, Flatpak support, New System font{{r|OS15}}\n|}\n\n[[GNOME]] and [[XFCE]] are currently the official desktop environments. [[XFCE]] is intended to be used mainly for the Lite Editions. Other desktop environments are also available for installation from the repos due to it being [[Ubuntu]]-based.\n\n==Security==\nZorin OS comes with the Uncomplicated Firewall installed, although it is not enabled by default.\n\n==Reception==\nZorin OS has been praised for its intuitive and familiar layouts, functionality, and installation process.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bidwell |first1=Jonni |title=Zorin OS 12 Core |url=https://www.techradar.com/reviews/zorin-os-12-core |website=TechRadar |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=22 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Zorin OS 12 Review: LinuxAndUbuntu Distro Review Of The Week |url=http://www.linuxandubuntu.com/home/zorin-os-12-review-linuxandubuntu-distro-review-of-the-week |website=LinuxAndUbuntu |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=2 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Fagioli |first1=Brian |title=Zorin OS 12.4 Linux distribution is here \u2013 switch from Microsoft Windows 10 now! |url=https://betanews.com/2018/08/14/zorin-os-124-linux/ |website=betanews |publisher=BetaNews, Inc |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=14 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://zorinos.com/ Zorin OS Website]\n* [https://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=zorin Zorin OS] on [[DistroWatch]]\n* [https://www.opensourcefeed.org/distribution/zorin Zorin OS on OpenSourceFeed Gallery]\n\n{{Ubuntu}}\n{{Linux distributions}}\n{{Linux}}\n{{Operating system}}\n\n[[Category:Operating systems]]\n[[Category:Ubuntu derivatives]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox OS\n| name = Zorin OS\n| logo = Zorin Logomark.svg\n| logo_size = 