ons, Flatpak support, New System font{{r|OS15}}\n|}\n\n[[GNOME]] and [[XFCE]] are currently the official desktop environments. [[XFCE]] is intended to be used mainly for the Lite Editions. Other desktop environments are also available for installation from the repos due to it being [[Ubuntu]]-based.\n\n==Security==\nZorin OS comes with the Uncomplicated Firewall installed, although it is not enabled by default.\n\n==Reception==\nZorin OS has been praised for its intuitive and familiar layouts, functionality, and installation process.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bidwell |first1=Jonni |title=Zorin OS 12 Core |url=https://www.techradar.com/reviews/zorin-os-12-core |website=TechRadar |publisher=Future plc |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=22 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Zorin OS 12 Review: LinuxAndUbuntu Distro Review Of The Week |url=http://www.linuxandubuntu.com/home/zorin-os-12-review-linuxandubuntu-distro-review-of-the-week |website=LinuxAndUbuntu |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=2 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Fagioli |first1=Brian |title=Zorin OS 12.4 Linux distribution is here \u2013 switch from Microsoft Windows 10 now! |url=https://betanews.com/2018/08/14/zorin-os-124-linux/ |website=betanews |publisher=BetaNews, Inc |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=English |date=14 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External Links==\n* [https://zorinos.com/ Zorin OS Website]\n* [https://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=zorin Zorin OS] on [[DistroWatch]]\n* [https://www.opensourcefeed.org/distribution/zorin Zorin OS on OpenSourceFeed Gallery]\n\n{{Ubuntu}}\n{{Linux distributions}}\n{{Linux}}\n{{Operating system}}\n\n[[Category:Operating systems]]\n[[Category:Ubuntu derivatives]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "cleanup", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zorin_OS"}
{"title_page": "NIO (car company)", "text_new": "{{About|the electric vehicles company|other uses|NIO (disambiguation){{!}}NIO (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Chinese car company}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = NIO Inc.\n|module = {{Chinese|child=yes|s=\u4e0a\u6d77\u851a\u6765\u6c7d\u8f66\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|t=\u4e0a\u6d77\u851a\u4f86\u6c7d\u8eca\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|p=Sh\u00e0ngh\u01cei W\u00e8il\u00e1i Q\u00ecch\u0113 Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b|altname=Business name|s2=\u851a\u6765\u6c7d\u8f66|t2=\u851a\u4f86\u6c7d\u8eca|l2=Sky-Blue Coming Motor Vehicles|p2=W\u00e8il\u00e1i Q\u00ecch\u0113|mi2={{IPAc-cmn|wei|4|l|ai|2|-|q|i|4|ch|e|1}}|order=st}}\n| logo = File:NIO_(Automobilhersteller)_logo.svg\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{NYSE|NIO}}<br>([[American Depository Receipt]]s)\n| industry = [[Automotive]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|2014|11}}\n| founder = [[William Li (businessman)|William Li]] (Li Bin)\n| location_city = [[Shanghai]]\n| location_country = China\n| num_locations = 4\n| area_served = {{ubl\n|China\n|Germany\n|Hong Kong\n|United Kingdom\n|United States\n}}\n| key_people = {{ubl \n|William Li ([[Chairman]] and [[CEO]])  \n|Lihong Qin ([[President (corporate title)|President]])\n|[[Wei Feng]] ([[CFO]])\n}}\n| revenue = {{increase}} {{US$|720.1 million|link=yes}} (2018)<ref name=AR18>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.nio.com/static-files/416025cc-9f06-4c8d-a9c4-d38657afd698|title=2018 Annual Report |website=www.nio.io|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n| operating_income = {{decrease}} {{US$|-1,395.6 million}}. (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| net_income = {{decrease}} {{US$|-1,401.9 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| assets =  {{increase}} {{US$|2,740.5 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| equity =  {{increase}} {{US$|992 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| owner = \n| num_employees =  Approx.  4,000 (2018)\n| divisions = [[NIO Formula E Team]]\n| website = {{url|https://www.nio.io|nio.io}}\n}}\n\n'''NIO''' ({{zh|c=\u851a\u6765|p=W\u00e8il\u00e1i}}) is a Chinese automobile manufacturer headquartered in [[Shanghai]], specializing in designing and developing [[Electric car|electric]] [[Self-driving car|autonomous vehicles]]. The company is also involved in the FIA [[Formula E]] Championship, the first single-seater, all-electric racing series.\n\n== Overview ==\nNIO was founded in November 2014 by William Li ({{zh|c=\u674e\u658c|p=L\u01d0 B\u012bn|links=no}}), the Chairman of Bitauto and [[NextEV Formula E Team|NextEV]]. After launch, several companies invested in NIO, including [[Tencent]], [[Temasek Holdings|Temasek]], [[Baidu]], [[Sequoia Capital|Sequoia]], [[Lenovo]] and [[TPG Capital|TPG]]. Its first model, the [[NIO EP9]] [[sports car]], debuted the same day the brand was established.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nIn October 2016, NIO announced that it had been given an \"Autonomous Vehicle Testing Permit\" by the [[California]] [[Department of Motor Vehicles|DMV]] and it would begin testing on public roads under the \"Autonomous Vehicle Tester Program\" guidelines as part of its [[Self-driving car|autonomous vehicle]] program. According to the company, it planned to launch vehicles with level-three and level-four autonomy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nio.io/news/nextev-issued-autonomous-vehicle-testing-permit-california|title=NIO - NextEV Issued Autonomous Vehicle Testing Permit in California|website=www.nio.io|language=en|access-date=2017-05-11}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, NIO opened its first battery swap station in the [[Nanshan District, Shenzhen|Nanshan District]] of [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong]], China, dubbed the \"Power Swap Station\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://insideevs.com/nio-opened-first-battery-swap-station-in-shenzhen/|title=NIO Opens First Battery Swap Station In Shenzhen|website=insideevs.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref> Only batteries for ES8 cars would be available from this station.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://insideevs.com/news/338117/nio-opens-first-battery-swap-station-in-shenzhen/|title=NIO announced that its first battery swap station - called the Power Swap Station - is now fully operational in the Nanshan Science and Technology Park, Shenzhen, China|publisher=Insidedeevs|author=Mark Kane|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, the company filed for a US$1.8 billion [[initial public offering]] on the [[New York Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehustle.co/Nio-IPO-China/|title=Chinese electric carmaker filed for a $1.8B IPO in the US after selling 481 cars with 15000 backlog. |date=2018-08-15 |work=The Hustle|access-date=2018-08-22}}</ref>\n\n== Technology ==\n=== NIO Pilot ===\nNIO Pilot is the company's SAE level 2 semi autonomous system that offers [[Advanced driver-assistance systems|ADAS]] features. It launched with the introduction of NIO's [[NIO ES8|ES8]] model. Several over the updates throughout 2018 and 2019\nhas enhanced NIO Pilot with features such as [[Lane centering|lane keeping]], [[adaptive cruise control]], [[Lane departure warning system|lane departure warning]], [[Automatic Emergency Braking|automatic emergency braking]], highway pilot, traffic Jam pilot, auto lane change and more.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.greencarcongress.com/2019/06/20190617-nio.html|title=NIO updates Level 2 advanced driving assistant system NIO Pilot|website=Green Car Congress|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nNIO Pilot sensor suite consists of a trifocal forward camera, 5 radars, 12 ultrasonic sensors and a driver monitor camera.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://equalocean.com/auto/20190611-nio-upgrades-autopilot-system-and-smart-operating-system|title=NIO Upgrades Autopilot System and Smart Operating System|website=EqualOcean|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> \nNIO was the first automaker to launch a car model utilizing [[Mobileye|Mobileye's EyeQ4]] vision chip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20171218005356/en/NIO-Launches-ES8-SUV-New-User-Experience|title=NIO Launches ES8 SUV with New User Experience|date=2017-12-18|website=www.businesswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2019, NIO announced a partnership with Mobileye to develop a consumer car equipped with Mobileye's complete Level 4 self driving system that could be sold to consumers by 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nio-autonomous-intel-idUSKBN1XF1YD|title=Nio, Mobileye partner on self-driving consumer passenger cars in China|date=2019-11-05|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en}}</ref>\n== Divisions ==\n=== NIO Life ===\nNIO Life is the company's clothing collection, made in collaboration with [[Hussein Chalayan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dezeen.com/2018/11/16/nio-clothing-hussein-chalayan-fashion-extreme-speed/|title=Nio and Hussein Chalayan launch clothing collection inspired by world's fastest electric car|author=de Klee, Katie|publisher=De Zeen|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n=== NIO Service ===\nNIO Service is the company's network of service centers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://electrek.co/2018/04/03/nio-electric-car-service-center-tesla/|title=NIO opens its first electric car service center right next to Tesla\u2019s|author=Lambert, Fred|publisher=Electrek|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n=== NIO Power ===\nNIO Power is the company's network of battery swap stations, power mobile, power home and super chargers. NIO has 122 Play Stations around China, including 18 battery swap stations along the [[G4 Beijing\u2013Hong Kong\u2013Macau Expressway|G4 Expressway]] in China.<ref name=electrekswap>{{cite news|url=https://electrek.co/2018/11/15/nio-battery-swap-stations-network/|title=Nio deploys 18 battery swap stations covering 2,000+ km expressway|author=Lambert, Fred|publisher=Electrek|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n== Vehicles ==\n\n=== Current models ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Model name\n! Photo\n! Specifications \n|-\n! [[NIO EP9|EP9]]\n| [[File:Nio EP9.jpg|frameless]]\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Coupe]]\n\n'''Class:''' [[Supercar#Hypercar|Hypercar]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 2\n\n'''Seats:''' 2\n\n'''Motor:''' Indirectly [[water cooling|water-cooled]] [[electric motors]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2016\u2013present \n|-\n! [[NIO ES6|ES6]]\n| [[File:Nio ES6 001.jpg|frameless]] \n| \n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Mid-size SUV|Mid-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2019\u2013present \n|-\n! [[NIO ES8|ES8]]\n| [[File:NIO ES8 01 China 2019-04-02.jpg|frameless]]\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Full-size SUV|Full-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 7\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2018\u2013present\n|}\n\n=== Upcoming models ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Model name\n! Photo \n!\n! Specifications\n|-\n! [[NIO EC6|EC6]] <ref>{{cite web | date = 29 December 2019 | url = https://www.chinapev.com/ev-2/nio/nio-debuts-new-ev-nio-ec6-is-a-coupe-suv-based-on-es6/ | title = NIO Debuts New EV: NIO EC6 Is a Coupe SUV Based on ES6 | work = ChinaPEV.com | accessdate = 29 December 2019}}</ref>\n|[https://www.electrive.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/nio-ec6-2020-03-min-888x444.png]\n|\n|\n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Mid-size SUV]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2020 (to commence) \n|-\n!\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n! [[NIO EF9|EF9]]\n| \n|\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Minivan]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[M-segment|M]]) [[Minivan]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 7/8\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2021 (to commence) \n|-\n! [[NIO ES3|ES3]]\n| \n|\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Subcompact SUV|Subcompact]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2021 (to commence)\n|-\n! [[NIO ET5|ET5]]\n|\n|\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[C-segment|C]]) [[Compact car|Compact]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 4\n\n'''Seats:''' 4\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2020 (to commence)\n|-\n![[NIO ET7|ET7]]\n|[[File:NIO_ET_Preview_Concept_001.jpg|frameless]]\n|\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[D-segment|D]]) [[Mid-size car|Mid-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 4\n\n'''Seats:''' 4\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2020 (to commence)\n|}\n\n=== Concept models ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Model name\n! Photo \n! Specifications\n|-\n! [[NIO ET Preview|ET Preview]]\n| [[File:NIO_ET_Preview_Concept_001.jpg|frameless]]\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Sedan (automobile)|Sedan]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[D-segment|D]]) [[Mid-size car|Mid-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 4\n\n'''Seats:''' 4\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2019 (previewing upcoming model)\n|-\n![[NIO Eve]]\n| [[File:NIO_Eve_concept_01.jpg|frameless]]\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Station wagon]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[C-segment|C]]) [[Compact car|Compact]] [[autonomous vehicle]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 2\n\n'''Seats:''' 4\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2017 (previewing a possible upcoming model)\n|}\n\n<!--===Production===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Country\n!Cars (2016)\n!Cars (2017)\n!Cars (2018)\n!Cars (2019)\n!Cars (2020)\n!Notes\n|-\n|'''[[NIO EP9|EP9]]'''<br />\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n| \n|-\n|'''[[NIO ES8|ES8]]'''<br />\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n| \n|-\n|'''[[NIO ES6|ES6]]'''<br />\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}-->\n\n==Battery swapping==\n[[File:Nio_ES8_front.jpg|thumb|right|Battery swapping was first available on the [[NIO ES8]]]]\nUnlike [[Tesla, Inc.|Tesla]], which has tried battery swapping but has never deployed it on a large scale and relies instead on its Supercharger network, Nio has built a functioning network of battery-swap stations that covers a few thousand kilometers of Chinese expressways.\n\nThe first phase was installing 18 battery-swap stations in 14 different places along the [[G4 Beijing\u2013Hong Kong\u2013Macau Expressway|G4 expressway]]. It is a {{convert|2273|km|mi|adj=mid|-long}} road connecting [[Beijing]] (the national capital) with the [[Pearl River Delta]] (world's largest urban area<ref>[http://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2015/01/26/world-bank-report-provides-new-data-to-help-ensure-urban-growth-benefits-the-poor World Bank Report Provides New Data to Help Ensure Urban Growth Benefits the Poor], The World Bank Group, 26 Jan 2015</ref> where [[Hong Kong]] and [[Shenzhen]] are located). This was completed in November 2018.<ref name=electrekswap/>\n\nThe second phase consisted of installing battery-swap stations in 8 locations along the [[G2 Beijing\u2013Shanghai Expressway|G2 expressway]], a {{convert|1212|km|mi|adj=mid|-long}} road connecting Beijing with [[Shanghai]]. This phase was completed in January 2019.<ref>https://twitter.com/NIOGlobal/status/1085431718679592960</ref>\n\n==Sales==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Calendar year\n!EP9\n!ES6<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carsalesbase.com/china-car-sales-data/nio/nio-es6/|title=NIO ES6 China Auto Sales Figures|publisher=CarSalesBase.com|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n!ES8<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carsalesbase.com/china-car-sales-data/nio/nio-es8/|title=NIO ES8 China Auto Sales Figures|publisher=CarSalesBase.com|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n!Total\n!Notes\n|-\n|2016\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|6\n|0\n|0\n|6\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|10*\n|0\n|8,101\n|8,111*\n|*Number not confirmed\n|-\n|2019\n|0\n|20,204\n|8,872\n|29,076\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|0*\n|1,493*\n|105*\n|1,598*\n|Sales drop in early 2020 due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]<br/>*As of January 2020\n|-\n|Total\n|16*\n|21,697*\n|17,078*\n|38,791*\n|*As of January 2020\n|}\n\n== Technologies ==\n\n=== NOMI AI===\n\nNOMI, an artificial-intelligence technology, claimed to be the first in-car AI system in production vehicles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.autodevot.com/2018/07/nio-starts-delivering-es8-electric-suvs-nomi-ai/|title=NIO starts delivering ES8 electric SUVs with NOMI AI|publisher=Autodevot|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref> NOMI can pull up the cars navigation, control the music, and unique to NIO cars can take a selfie of the passengers in the cabin.\n\n== Motorsport ==\n===Formula E===\n{{main|NIO Formula E Team}}\n[[File:Nio Formula E car.jpg|thumb|220x220px|NIO have been participating in the [[Formula E|ABB FIA Formula E]] since 2014, the inaugural season.]]\n\nNIO first joined the [[Formula E]] championship series in its inaugural [[2014\u201315 Formula E season|2014\u20132015 season]] with their counterpart formerly known as [[NIO Formula E Team|China Racing Formula E Team]]. For the season, the team had [[Ho-Pin Tung]] and [[Charles Pic]] drive the #88 car, and Brazilian driver [[Nelson Piquet Jr.]] drive the #99 car. They team went on to win the inaugural FIA Formula E Drivers' Championship in July 2015 with [[Nelson Piquet Jr.]], and also winning two races, the [[2015 Long Beach ePrix]] and the [[2015 Moscow ePrix]].\n\nThe second season in the Formula E, allowed teams to be able to develop new powertrains for the season. The team used its own NextEV chassis and powertrains for the season.\n\nFrom the inaugural season of the series to present, NextEV has not won a Constructors' Championship yet and has yet to win one, but has won a Drivers' Championship, and two races, the [[2015 Long Beach ePrix]] and the [[2015 Moscow ePrix]], both races from the [[2014\u201315 Formula E season|2014\u20132015 Formula E season]]. NIO secured the inaugural FIA Formula E Drivers's Championship in July 2015.\n\n== World records ==\n\nNIO set five records in their track-only EP9 for the fastest lap for an electric-powered car in the [[N\u00fcrburgring Nordschleife]], [[Circuit Paul Ricard]], [[Circuit of the Americas]], and [[Shanghai International Circuit]] tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/electric/video-watch-nio-ep9s-645-ring-record|title=Video: watch the Nio EP9\u2019s 6:45 \u2018Ring record|website=www.topgear.com|language=en|access-date=2018-03-24}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Aion (car brand)|Aion]]\n* [[BYD Auto|BYD]]\n* [[Byton (company)|Byton]]\n* [[Faraday Future]]\n* [[Fisker Inc.]]\n* [https://www.human-horizons.com/ Human Horizons]\n* [[Lucid Motors]]\n* [[Lynk & Co]]\n* [[Polestar]]\n* [[Rivian]]\n* [[Tesla, Inc.]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://www.nio.io}}\n{{Finance links\n| name = NIO Inc.\n| symbol = NIO\n| reuters = NIO.N\n| bloomberg = NIO:US\n| sec_cik = NIO\n| yahoo = NIO\n| google = NIO\n}}\n\n{{Nio (car company)}}\n{{NIO automobile timeline}}\n{{Automotive industry in China}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Electric vehicle manufacturers of China]]\n[[Category:Car brands]]\n[[Category:Car manufacturers of China]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies based in Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in China]]\n[[Category:Vehicle manufacturing companies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:Chinese companies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:2018 initial public offerings]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:NIO (car company)]]\n[[Category:Chinese brands]]\n[[Category:Luxury motor vehicle manufacturers]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the electric vehicles company|other uses|NIO (disambiguation){{!}}NIO (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Chinese car company}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = NIO Inc.\n|module = {{Chinese|child=yes|s=\u4e0a\u6d77\u851a\u6765\u6c7d\u8f66\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|t=\u4e0a\u6d77\u851a\u4f86\u6c7d\u8eca\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8|p=Sh\u00e0ngh\u01cei W\u00e8il\u00e1i Q\u00ecch\u0113 Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b|altname=Business name|s2=\u851a\u6765\u6c7d\u8f66|t2=\u851a\u4f86\u6c7d\u8eca|l2=Sky-Blue Coming Motor Vehicles|p2=W\u00e8il\u00e1i Q\u00ecch\u0113|mi2={{IPAc-cmn|wei|4|l|ai|2|-|q|i|4|ch|e|1}}|order=st}}\n| logo = File:NIO_(Automobilhersteller)_logo.svg\n| type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{NYSE|NIO}}<br>([[American Depository Receipt]]s)\n| industry = [[Automotive]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|2014}}\n| founder = [[William Li (businessman)|William Li]] (Li Bin)\n| location_city = [[Shanghai]]\n| location_country = China\n| num_locations = 4\n| area_served = {{ubl\n|China\n|Germany\n|Hong Kong\n|United Kingdom\n|United States\n}}\n| key_people = {{ubl \n|William Li ([[Chairman]] and [[CEO]])  \n|Lihong Qin ([[President (corporate title)|President]])\n|[[Wei Feng]] ([[CFO]])\n}}\n| revenue = {{increase}} {{US$|720.1 million|link=yes}} (2018)<ref name=AR18>{{Cite web|url=https://ir.nio.com/static-files/416025cc-9f06-4c8d-a9c4-d38657afd698|title=2018 Annual Report |website=www.nio.io|language=en|access-date=2019-05-04}}</ref>\n| operating_income = {{decrease}} {{US$|-1,395.6 million}}. (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| net_income = {{decrease}} {{US$|-1,401.9 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| assets =  {{increase}} {{US$|2,740.5 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| equity =  {{increase}} {{US$|992 million}} (2018)<ref name=AR18/>\n| owner = \n| num_employees =  Approx.  4,000 (2018)\n| divisions = [[NIO Formula E Team]]\n| website = {{url|https://www.nio.io|nio.io}}\n}}\n\n'''NIO''' ({{zh|c=\u851a\u6765|p=W\u00e8il\u00e1i}}) is a Chinese automobile manufacturer headquartered in [[Shanghai]], specializing in designing and developing [[Electric car|electric]] [[Self-driving car|autonomous vehicles]]. The company is also involved in the FIA [[Formula E]] Championship, the first single-seater, all-electric racing series.\n\n== Overview ==\nNIO was founded in November 2014 by William Li ({{zh|c=\u674e\u658c|p=L\u01d0 B\u012bn|links=no}}), the Chairman of Bitauto and [[NextEV Formula E Team|NextEV]]. After launch, several companies invested in NIO, including [[Tencent]], [[Temasek Holdings|Temasek]], [[Baidu]], [[Sequoia Capital|Sequoia]], [[Lenovo]] and [[TPG Capital|TPG]]. Its first model, the [[NIO EP9]] [[sports car]], debuted the same day the brand was established.{{citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\nIn October 2016, NIO announced that it had been given an \"Autonomous Vehicle Testing Permit\" by the [[California]] [[Department of Motor Vehicles|DMV]] and it would begin testing on public roads under the \"Autonomous Vehicle Tester Program\" guidelines as part of its [[Self-driving car|autonomous vehicle]] program. According to the company, it planned to launch vehicles with level-three and level-four autonomy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nio.io/news/nextev-issued-autonomous-vehicle-testing-permit-california|title=NIO - NextEV Issued Autonomous Vehicle Testing Permit in California|website=www.nio.io|language=en|access-date=2017-05-11}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, NIO opened its first battery swap station in the [[Nanshan District, Shenzhen|Nanshan District]] of [[Shenzhen]], [[Guangdong]], China, dubbed the \"Power Swap Station\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://insideevs.com/nio-opened-first-battery-swap-station-in-shenzhen/|title=NIO Opens First Battery Swap Station In Shenzhen|website=insideevs.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref> Only batteries for ES8 cars would be available from this station.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://insideevs.com/news/338117/nio-opens-first-battery-swap-station-in-shenzhen/|title=NIO announced that its first battery swap station - called the Power Swap Station - is now fully operational in the Nanshan Science and Technology Park, Shenzhen, China|publisher=Insidedeevs|author=Mark Kane|accessdate=9 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2018, the company filed for a US$1.8 billion [[initial public offering]] on the [[New York Stock Exchange]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehustle.co/Nio-IPO-China/|title=Chinese electric carmaker filed for a $1.8B IPO in the US after selling 481 cars with 15000 backlog. |date=2018-08-15 |work=The Hustle|access-date=2018-08-22}}</ref>\n\n== Technology ==\n=== NIO Pilot ===\nNIO Pilot is the company's SAE level 2 semi autonomous system that offers [[Advanced driver-assistance systems|ADAS]] features. It launched with the introduction of NIO's [[NIO ES8|ES8]] model. Several over the updates throughout 2018 and 2019\nhas enhanced NIO Pilot with features such as [[Lane centering|lane keeping]], [[adaptive cruise control]], [[Lane departure warning system|lane departure warning]], [[Automatic Emergency Braking|automatic emergency braking]], highway pilot, traffic Jam pilot, auto lane change and more.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.greencarcongress.com/2019/06/20190617-nio.html|title=NIO updates Level 2 advanced driving assistant system NIO Pilot|website=Green Car Congress|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nNIO Pilot sensor suite consists of a trifocal forward camera, 5 radars, 12 ultrasonic sensors and a driver monitor camera.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://equalocean.com/auto/20190611-nio-upgrades-autopilot-system-and-smart-operating-system|title=NIO Upgrades Autopilot System and Smart Operating System|website=EqualOcean|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> \nNIO was the first automaker to launch a car model utilizing [[Mobileye|Mobileye's EyeQ4]] vision chip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20171218005356/en/NIO-Launches-ES8-SUV-New-User-Experience|title=NIO Launches ES8 SUV with New User Experience|date=2017-12-18|website=www.businesswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2019, NIO announced a partnership with Mobileye to develop a consumer car equipped with Mobileye's complete Level 4 self driving system that could be sold to consumers by 2022.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-nio-autonomous-intel-idUSKBN1XF1YD|title=Nio, Mobileye partner on self-driving consumer passenger cars in China|date=2019-11-05|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-12|language=en}}</ref>\n== Divisions ==\n=== NIO Life ===\nNIO Life is the company's clothing collection, made in collaboration with [[Hussein Chalayan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dezeen.com/2018/11/16/nio-clothing-hussein-chalayan-fashion-extreme-speed/|title=Nio and Hussein Chalayan launch clothing collection inspired by world's fastest electric car|author=de Klee, Katie|publisher=De Zeen|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n=== NIO Service ===\nNIO Service is the company's network of service centers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://electrek.co/2018/04/03/nio-electric-car-service-center-tesla/|title=NIO opens its first electric car service center right next to Tesla\u2019s|author=Lambert, Fred|publisher=Electrek|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n=== NIO Power ===\nNIO Power is the company's network of battery swap stations, power mobile, power home and super chargers. NIO has 122 Play Stations around China, including 18 battery swap stations along the [[G4 Beijing\u2013Hong Kong\u2013Macau Expressway|G4 Expressway]] in China.<ref name=electrekswap>{{cite news|url=https://electrek.co/2018/11/15/nio-battery-swap-stations-network/|title=Nio deploys 18 battery swap stations covering 2,000+ km expressway|author=Lambert, Fred|publisher=Electrek|accessdate=2019-04-24}}</ref>\n\n== Vehicles ==\n\n=== Current models ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Model name\n! Photo\n! Specifications \n|-\n! [[NIO EP9|EP9]]\n| [[File:Nio EP9.jpg|frameless]]\n| \n'''Body style:''' [[Coupe]]\n\n'''Class:''' [[Supercar#Hypercar|Hypercar]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 2\n\n'''Seats:''' 2\n\n'''Motor:''' Indirectly [[water cooling|water-cooled]] [[electric motors]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2016\u2013present \n|-\n! [[NIO ES6|ES6]]\n| [[File:Nio ES6 001.jpg|frameless]] \n| \n'''Body style:''' [[SUV]]\n\n'''Class:''' ([[J-segment|J]]) [[Mid-size SUV|Mid-size]]\n\n'''Doors:''' 5\n\n'''Seats:''' 5\n\n'''Battery:''' [[Lithium-ion battery]]\n\n'''Production:''' 2019\u2013present \n|-\n! [[NIO ES8|ES8]]\